{{Infobox University |name=University of Carthage |native_name=جامعة قرطاج |image=<!-- Commented out because image was deleted: [[File:unicarth.jpg|100px|Logo of the Carthage University]] --> |latin_name= |established=1988 |type=[[Public university|Public]] |staff= |rector=Pr Lassaâd Asmi<ref>{{fr icon}} [http://www.lapresse.tn/11022013/34132/les-nouveaux-presidents-duniversite.html The new tunisian universities chancellors ] {{webarchive|url=https://archive.is/20130418175354/http://www.lapresse.tn/11022013/34132/les-nouveaux-presidents-duniversite.html |date=2013-04-18 }}</ref> |faculty= |students=48634 |city=[[Tunis]] |country=[[Tunisia]] | former_names = Carthage 7 November University | campus= |affiliations= [[Mediterranean Universities Union|UNIMED]] |website=[http://www.ucar.rnu.tn/ www.ucar.rnu.tn/] | }}
The '''University of [[Carthage]]''' ({{lang-ar|جامعة قرطاج}}) is a university located in [[Tunis]], [[Tunisia]]. It was founded in 1988.
==Organization== Carthage University is formed by 21 institutions under single-supervision and 12 under joint-supervision. The first category is composed by:<ref>[http://www.ucar.rnu.tn/data_en/index_en.php Carthage University Institutions] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121205192141/http://www.ucar.rnu.tn/data_en/index_en.php |date=December 5, 2012 }}</ref> * Faculty of Juridical, Political and Social Sciences, Tunis * Faculty of Sciences, Bizerte * Faculty of Economic Sciences and Management, Nabeul * National School of Architecture and Urbanism, Tunis * [[Tunisia Polytechnic School]] * Higher School of Technology and Computer Science * Higher School of Statistics and Information Analysis * The Gammarth Higher Institute of Audiovisual and Film Studies * Bizerte Preparatory Engineering Institute * Institute of Advanced Business Studies, Carthage *[[ National Institute of Applied Science and Technology]] * Higher Institute of Applied Sciences and Technology, Mateur * Nabeul Preparatory Engineering Institute * Preparatory Institute for Scientific and Technical Studies, La Marsa * Higher Institute of Fine Arts, Nabeul * Higher Institute of Environment, Urbanism and Building Technologies * Higher Institute of Languages, Tunis * Higher Institute of Applied Languages and Computer Science of Nabeul * Higher Institute of Sciences and Technology of Environment of Borj Cedria * Higher Institute of Business and Accountancy of Bizerte * National Engineering School of Bizerte
The second category contains basically: * [[Higher School of Communication of Tunis]]
