{{Infobox software |name = |logo = Lon-capa logo.PNG |developer = [[Michigan State University]] |operating_system = [[Cross-platform]] | programming language = [[Perl]] |genre = [[Course Management System]] |license = [[GNU General Public License|GPL]] |website = [http://lon-capa.org lon-capa.org] }}
'''LON-CAPA''' (Learning Online Network with Computer-Assisted Personalized Approach) is an [[e-learning]] platform, also known as a Course Management System (CMS) or Learning Management System ([[Learning management system|LMS]]). It possesses the standard features of many learning platforms (user roles, [[calendar]], [[e-mail]], [[chat room]]s, [[blog]]s, resource construction, test grading, etc.), but it differs from traditional e-learning platforms in that its many [[web server]]s (in various parts of the world) can communicate with each other.<ref name='campussource'>{{cite web |url=http://www.campussource.de/org/software/loncapa/ |title=LON-CAPA |accessdate=2007-11-30 |last= |first= |authorlink= |coauthors= |date= |format= |work= |publisher=CampusSource |pages= |quote= }}</ref> Consequently, the term LON-CAPA can also refer to the LON-CAPA network, i.e. the entire set of LON-CAPA web servers and the specific implementation of an internet [[Protocol (computing)|protocol]] that connects these web servers.<ref name='nf'>{{cite web |url=http://www.lon-capa.org/networkfeatures.html |title=Network Features |accessdate=2007-11-30 |last= |first= |authorlink= |coauthors= |date= |work= |publisher=LON-CAPA |pages= |quote= }}</ref> LON-CAPA can also refer to the LON-CAPA project, i.e. the core team of scientists and programmers that develop and maintain the LON-CAPA [[computer software|software]].
There are, as of 2010, more than 160 LON-CAPA domains, where a domain is a unified set of LON-CAPA web servers.<ref name='nf'/> LON-CAPA domains are operated, generally speaking, by individual [[university|universities]] and [[high school]]s in the [[United States]] and [[Canada]], but include private organizations and a significant number of universities in [[Europe]], [[Asia]], [[South America]] and [[Africa]].<ref name='nf'/> The LON-CAPA network allows participating universities and schools to create learning resources (test problems, [[web page]]s, etc.) and to share them across the network. This [[Collaboration|collaborative]] aspect is LON-CAPA's most distinctive feature.<ref name='campussource'/>
Another special feature of LON-CAPA is the ability to design test resources (called problems) that make use of [[random number generation|random numbers]] (stored in [[Perl]] [[Variable (programming)|variables]]). This allows a single "problem resource" to generate a variety of similar (but different) test exercises, thus significantly reducing the risk of cheating amongst students.<ref name='newsforge'>{{cite web |url=http://www.linux.com/articles/54225 |title=Open source package passes personal learning test |accessdate=2007-11-30 |last=Gasperson |first=Tina |authorlink= |coauthors= |date=2006-05-17 |format= |work= |publisher=Linux.com |pages= |quote= }}</ref>
Currently, the great majority of LON-CAPA's learning resources are written in English and focus on the [[mathematics|mathematical]] and [[natural science]]s, mostly significantly [[physics]] and [[chemistry]].<ref name='campussource'/> The learning platform works extensively with [[LaTeX]], a language used to represent [[formula]]s and mathematical expressions. The project is funded by the [[National Science Foundation]] (NSF).<ref name='sloanc'>{{cite web|url=http://sloan-c.org/effective/details4.asp?FS_ID=45 |title=Practice: Computer-Assisted Personalized Assignments, Quizzes, and Examinations |accessdate=2007-11-30 |last=Moore |first=Janet |authorlink= |coauthors= |date=2003-11-19 |format= |work= |publisher=The Sloan Consortium |pages= |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071108075659/http://www.sloan-c.org/effective/details4.asp?FS_ID=45 |archivedate=2007-11-08 |quote= |deadurl=yes |df= }}</ref>
LON-CAPA is [[Open-source software|open source]] and free of licensing fees.<ref name='sloanc'/> Significant technologies include [[Linux]], [[Apache HTTP Server|Apache]], [[mod perl]], [[MySQL]], [[LaTeX]] and [[CPAN]]. The core LON-CAPA development team is based at [[Michigan State University]] in [[East Lansing]], [[Michigan]].<ref name='newsforge'/> There are also major LON-CAPA [[Node (networking)|network nodes]] at [[Simon Fraser University]], the [[University of Illinois at Urbana-Champaign]], and [[Purdue University]].<ref name='purdue'>[http://www.itap.purdue.edu/learning/tools/loncapa/index.html ITaP LON-CAPA Information Page] 2015</ref>
The name LON-CAPA is an [[acronym]], derived from <u>L</u>earning <u>O</u>nline <u>N</u>etwork with <u>C</u>omputer-<u>A</u>ssisted <u>P</u>ersonalized <u>A</u>pproach. In 1999, two distinct e-learning projects, CAPA and LectureOnline, joined efforts in the creation of LON-CAPA, which provides a superset of the CAPA and LectureOnline functionalities.<ref name='newsforge'/>
