==Aircraft fleet==
=== NRC's Current fleet of research and test aircraft === The NRC has a fleet of nine aircraft for their research purposes:<ref>[https://www.nrc-cnrc.gc.ca/eng/solutions/facilities/research_aircraft.html Research aircraft fleet]</ref><ref name="TCFleet">{{TCregister|GOVERNMENT+OF+CANADA%2c+NATIONAL+RESEARCH+COUNCIL|Government Of Canada, National Research Council|2018-10-16}}</ref> * [[Bell 412]] – Advanced Systems Research Aircraft and 4-DOF simulator * [[Bell 204/205|Bell 205]] ([[Bell 205#Bell 205A-1|205A-1]]) – 4-DOF simulator * [[Bell 206]] ([[Bell 206#Bell 206B|206B]]) – Rotary trainer and advanced vision studies
* [[Canadair CT-133 Silver Star]] ([[Canadair CT-133 Silver Star#Silver Star Mk 3|Mk 3]]) – Vintage fighter jet * [[Convair CV-240 family|Convair 580]] – Multi-purpose flying laboratory * [[Dassault Falcon 20|Falcon 20]] (Mystère 20) – Aerospace, geoscience testing and micro gravity testing * [[de Havilland Canada DHC-6 Twin Otter|Twin Otter]] ([[de Havilland Canada DHC-6 Twin Otter#DHC-6 Series 200|Series 200]]) – Atmospheric and biospheric studies, and for flight mechanics and flight systems development
* [[Extra EA-300|Extra 300]] ([[Extra EA-300#300L|300L]]) – studying pilot perception in a dynamic environment and trainer
* [[North American T-6 Texan|Harvard]] ([[North American T-6 Texan variants#Harvard 4|4]]) – Trainer and experimental platform for avionics research
=== NRC's past fleet of research and test aircraft === Former aircraft include other models of the nine listed above<ref>[http://wwwapps.tc.gc.ca/Saf-Sec-Sur/2/CCARCS-RIACC/RchHsRes.aspx?st=2&m=%7C%7C&cn=%7C%7C&mn=%7C%7C&sn=%7C%7C&cnn=%7CGOVERNMENT%20OF%20CANADA,%20NATIONAL%20RESEARCH%20COUNCIL%7C&tn=%7C%7C&ln=%7C%7C&fn=%7C%7C&rfr2=RchHs.aspx&print=y Canadian Civil Aircraft Register: History Search Result]</ref> and the following:{{fact|date=October 2018}} * [[Beechcraft Model 18|C-45]] – Atmospheric studies (retired in 1992)
* [[Bell 47]] – Fly by wire and icing studies (last of 3 retired in the mid 1990s) * [[Canadair North Star]] – Similar work as the Convair 580. (Retired 1974) * [[de Havilland Canada DHC-5 Buffalo]] – High wing super [[STOL]] aircraft joint project with [[United States Air Force]] * [[de Havilland Canada DHC-1 Chipmunk]] * [[Beechcraft Queen Air]] – Retired from fleet pre 1980
